11 Sep 18, McDonnell begins to lay out his plans to attack private enterprise and give unions power again (to mess everything up). see https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/09/11/john-mcdonnell-pledges-return-power-unions-biggest-overhaul/   REVIEW THIS ARTICLE  TO PRODUCE VIDEO DEMONSTRATING THE COMMUNIST RULE OF INVERSES, everything he says will in fact work in the opposite and destructive direction. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">"The disguise has come off John McDonnell," said David Starkey, the historian. "He’s a revolutionary communist.”  This was on 7 Aug 2019 after McDonnell said he would send Corbyn to the Queen to demand she made him Prime Minister (if Boris Johnson lost a No Confidence Vote).
See full article at https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2019/08/07/john-mcdonnell-threatens-march-palace-tell-queen-taking-boris1/

A communist, supporter of Sinn Fein/IRA and of postmodern neo-Marxism. He attended the FARC activist mtg in Westminster in Apr 2014. 

After moving from his native Liverpool to East Anglia as a child, much of the shadow chancellor’s teenage years were spent at Great Yarmouth Grammar School - an experience, he says, which helped cultivate his long-standing opposition to selective education.

However, until recently, it was a well-kept secret that Mr McDonnell had later gone on to study at St Joseph’s College, a £12,500 a year independent boarding school, where he began - and later withdrew - from training to become a member of the clergy.
See 23 Aug 18 article in DT, https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/08/23/labours-public-schoolboys-jeremy-corbyn-accused-hypocrisy-calls/

Manifesto produced by the Inst of Employment Rights end-Dec 2017, a blueprint for Labour policy, incl returning to the pre-1970s laws allowing unions to run amok. 
He was Corbyn's election campaign manager, see https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/15/jeremy-corbyn-world-supporters-mentors-influences and is key to the new LP. 

See here (a site about the Left) for a full biography https://www.revolvy.com/main/index.php?s=John+McDonnell 

McDonnell was a supporter of Militant in the 80s and may have been a supporter of The Socialist Party which was the successor to Militant, which still operates. Some think Momentum is Militant 2.0

He is chairman of the Labour Representation Committee (LRC), a hard left group from which most of Corbyn's staffers are recruited. 

A strong supporter of the IRA and a strong supporter of Labour Committee on Ireland, LCI, the hard left pro republican group. McDonnell was pleased to receive a Hunger Strike commemorative plaque from Gerry Kelly who was the IRA terrorist who bombed the Old Bailey, killing one and injuring almost 200.  Kelly, now a senior Sinn Fein politician, also led the 1983 breakout of IRA inmates from the Maze prison, during which he shot a prison officer in the head. See photo in 
http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/Jeremy_Corbyn/11924431/Revealed-Jeremy-Corbyn-and-John-McDonnells-close-IRA-links.html  

In this article of the DT, McDonnell told the IRA’s official newspaper, An Phoblacht: “An assembly is not what people have laid down their lives for over thirty years. We want peace, but the settlement must be just and the settlement must be for an agreed and united Ireland.”   A united Ireland? Break up the Union? That IS what McDonnell would do... he said so. 

Of the IRA, McD said, "It's about time we started honouring those people involved in the armed struggle. It was the bombs and bullets and sacrifice made by the likes of Bobby Sands that brought Britain to the negotiating table. The peace we have now is due to the action of the IRA"  He received a plaque from his friend Gerry Kelly who is a convicted IRA terrorist. See bio at 
In fact, he later apologised for these remarks, but was that simply to cover his tracks? isn't he still an avowed republican with a strong Catholic bias who has always supported the IRA? see https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/09/17/john-mcdonnell-apologises_n_8155340.html  

Of MI5 and armed British Police,  "In 2015, McDonnell's name appeared on a letter calling for the armed police and MI5 to be disbanded. He claimed that he had not signed the letter, which was produced by the Socialist Campaign for a Labour Victory (SCLV), but he was photographed holding a copy of the letter, although he later said that he did not know that the demand was on the letter" (in Revolvy)

27 Feb 18, ref Labour's new idea for Brexit, to stay in the Customs Union but negotiate for the EU to agree to let UK do deals across the world (which simply won't be agreed by the EU) is economic lunacy... see Ambrose Evans Pritchard https://www.telegraph.co.uk/business/2018/02/26/corbyns-customs-union-traps-uk-economic-limbo-without-solving/ 

Says, "I want to be in a situation where no Tory can show their face anywhere without being challenged by direct action."
https://twitter.com/Jamin2g/status/959541145226436608?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;ref_url=http%3A%2F%2Fyour-brexit.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fheres-why-corbyn-and-mcdonnell-are-to-blame-for-rees-mogg-being-attacked%2F

