Naturally, McDONNELL spoke at a conference celebrating Karl Marx's 200th birthday, saying Marxism a “force for change today” https://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/article/marxism-a-force-for-change-today-john-mcdonnell-tells-marx-200-conference and naturally too the event took place at SOAS in London. 

John McDonnell seems to be a fan of Frederic Jameson, an American postmodern neo-Marxist, in an interview on BBC Newsnight on Tuesday 17 May 2016, and said, “I don’t believe capitalism serves the interest of our country at the moment. I want to transform our economic system. That means transforming capitalism.”
see https://www.rt.com/uk/343426-capitalism-neoliberalism-john-mcdonnell/

And Jameson has had a huge influence in China, see also Zhang Yiwu in this chart, so is McDonnell planning to recreate Britain on a model of what China has become or at least what it would be if it adopts the ideas of people like Yiwu?

Novara media ct say McDonnell is quite right to praise Karl Marx https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o4J0lEcQJiw  

Corbyn, Lansman, McDonnell and Shawcroft were greatly influenced by Vladimir Derer who worked tirelessly to replace the influence of the PLP by that of the members themselves, out there, voting for what they want, which is not necessarily at all what the LP MPs want or what Parliament itself wants.  See interesting explan at https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/09/understand-jeremy-corbyn-look-first-vladimir-derer
and on how these people worked on BRIEFING, a radical Left magazine which alongside the CLPD which Derer got established, has been the engine behind Corbynism over the years. 
This originally emerged as a splinter group from the Trotskyist Chartist Tendency. 
Derer and Briefing could be referred to as Neo-Chartists, as they built upon the work of the original radical chartists of the 19th century who sought to bring about transformative change through constitutional reform.  Corbyn, John McDonnell and Christine Shawcroft, who currently sit on the NEC, were all and continue to be leading lights in the magazine.
Is not Derer's advice to increase State ownership also the way McDonnell wants to go?

See this 10 January 1986 edition of the South African political organ Socialist Action in which there are articles by an interesting group of people; Derer (defending Militant in Liverpool, McDonnell's stamping ground, and in Lambeth), Corbyn, Abbott, 

7 Sep 18, Top Corbynistas are openly referring to John McDonnell by his IRA nickname “The Quartermaster”. Momentum man Max Shanly called the Shadow Chancellor by his IRA nom de guerre on this week’s Novara Media All The Best podcast. Appearing alongside former Corbyn spokesman Matt Zarb-Cousin, Shanly said:  “I went to John McDonnell’s Alternative Models of Ownership Conference this weekend… it was very interesting, I don’t know how many of you have read the Alternative Models of Ownership report commissioned by The Quartermaster and Rebecca Long-Bailey, but it’s a very good read.”  See https://order-order.com/tag/novara-media/

