15 Sep 18, this article by Phillip Hammond spells out why the Corbyn-McDonnell plans for UK's economy would be an absolute disaster. Socialism always spends other people's money till it runs out, but this pair's neo-Marxist ideology would make that happen to a degree never seen in the UK before. Labour’s economic philosophy is endless spending, increased centralisation and mounting debt, leading to total bankruptcy.  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/09/14/corbyn-makes-gordon-brown-look-like-scrooge-marxist-manifesto/?li_source=LI&amp;li_medium=li-recommendation-widget  and McDonnell's costs will be 176 Bn... colossal, which the country does NOT have... http://www.cps.org.uk/publications/the-cost-of-nationalisation.   Since all this, his plans seem to add up to a cost nearer 500 Bn, as judged by his speeches at the Sep 2018 Labour Conference. He will nee to double all taxes to get anywhere near paying for his plans.

26 Sep 18, At the LP conference, McDonnell laid out his plans to involve Labour in every reasonable sized company in the country... see this piece in Labour List https://labourlist.org/2018/09/mcdonnell-sets-out-plans-for-staff-to-share-ownership-of-large-companies/ 
and this critique by Letts in the Daily Mail https://www.dailymail.co.uk/debate/article-6212061/Dont-scoff-Comrade-Corbyn-says-QUENTIN-LETTS.html?ns_mchannel=rss&amp;ito=1490&amp;ns_campaign=1490  

