5 Jun 19, so neo-Marxist Labour have finally produced a report which says private land ownership should be reviewed if Labour reach government, proposing, "radical... changes in the way land in the UK is used and governed." The blazing omission in this sentence is that land is currently OWNED. So, here is Labour's plan, to carry out what Karl Marx advised in his Communist Manifesto... attack private ownership of land and property.   https://landforthemany.uk

23 Jun 19. Labour plans to tax ownership of land to the limit... on everyone's ownership of land. The idea, put forward in a report called Land for the Many comes alongside other suggestions, including replacing inheritance tax (IHT) with a “lifetime gifts tax” levied on recipients at the marginal rate, with an allowance of just £125,000 of protections – less than half the current £325,000 under IHT – and abolishing the “family home allowance” that gives additional protections of up to £175,000 if a property is being passed to a direct descendant.  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/opinion/2019/06/23/labours-wealth-grab-would-iniquitous-country/#comments

27 Jul 2019, Major law firm assesses that Labour's economic plans will double the tax burden on British companies.  The figures are based on new calculations by the firm showing that Mr Corbyn's planned mandatory share ownership scheme for large companies would cost businesses the equivalent of up to 6 per cent in additional corporation tax. Business leaders had previously warned that the policy would turn investors away from the UK  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2019/07/27/jeremy-corbyn-planning-almost-double-tax-burden-british-businesses/

