<data key="bio &amp; notes">Hard left union leader, who is ready to see the Labour Party get into power by any (legal, or possibly illegal) means. 

Hard left activist with international connections.  For example, he invited the Justice for Colombia group to his UNITE conference in July 2014, see http://www.justiceforcolombia.org/news/article/1664/jfc-hosts-colombian-trade-unionist-at-unite-conference 

He has a strong grip on Corbyn who needs UNITE's support, and close links to Corbyn's key staff member Karie Murphy, see http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/jeremy-corbyn-unions-len-mccluskey-unite-election-blairite-mps-gerard-coyne-future-a7680706.html

Len shared a flat at one time with Tom Watson. Was this the same flat for which Len used UNITE funds to contribute to the cost, which he then rather quietly paid back when Gerard Coyne made a fuss? https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/feb/26/len-mccluskey-repays-400000-unite-put-towards-his-flat

Gerard Coyne, whom Len beat for leadership of UNITE, is making formal complaints to have the contest overturned... the case will be heard on either 20 or 27 March 18. see https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/work/trade-unions/news/91582/unite-deny-len-mccluskey-quit-retired-judge-appointed-probe-his

What is clear is that Red Len's mandate is very thin in fact: McCluskey won 59,067 votes (45.4%) compared with Coyne’s 53,544 (41.5%), on a turnout of just over 12%, a closer result than expected. Only 130,071 members voted out of a claimed membership of 1.42 million. This chronic and utterly undemocratic election performance means that a mere 9.16% of members voted and a pathetic 4.16% voted for McCluskey.  One can only imagine the noise he would make if the Prime Minister took over the government with a similarly derisory vote count!

Apr 2018, Red Len complains about the anti-semitic slurs against Corbyn, threatening other LP MPs who have been confirming this feature of the hard left. see this and his biography in... https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/04/26/like-trot-len-mccluskey-will-defend-corbyn-hilt-corbyn-falls/?li_source=LI&amp;li_medium=li-recommendation-widget





