<data key="bio &amp; notes">Lifetime marxist activist.
In the run up to the 2017 general election, Corbyn said that he had "never met the IRA", although Shadow Home Secretary Diane Abbott (who was in a relationship with Corbyn) later clarified that although he had met members of the IRA, "he met with them in their capacity as activists in Sinn Fein"  See PoliticsHome.com (27 May 2017). "Diane Abbott: Corbyn met IRA members 'in their capacity as Sinn Fein activists'". Archived from the original on 27 May 2017.

A strong supporter of the IRA and a strong supporter of Labour Committee on Ireland, LCI, the hard left pro republican group.  In 1984, Abbott said Ireland, “is our struggle – every defeat of the British state is a victory for all of us. A defeat in Northern Ireland would be a defeat indeed.” Abbott, then a Labour councillor, added: “Though I was born here in London, I couldn’t identify as British.”  https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/may/28/diane-abbott-under-fire--afro-remark-questioned-about-ira

She is also an enthusiastic supporter of Antifa. The Labour MP for Hackney North and Stoke Newington was among those who travelled to Dover to join the Antifa protest in January 2016.

Abbott is another left-wing hypocrite. She volubly criticised both Tony Blair and Harriet Harman for sending their children to selective state schools. But sent her own son, not to a selective state school, but to a full-blown fee-paying public school.

Actually, Abbott's hypocrisy is breath-taking, see Guardian article https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/may/28/diane-abbott-under-fire--afro-remark-questioned-about-ira 

She has defended Mao Tse Tung, saying he did “more good than harm”.  And called the Home Office “fundamentally the most racist organisation in the world”. And was taken to a task on Question Time by a furious audience member who demanded she apologise for branding Leave voters racist. In July 2017, she even branded supporters of fossil fuel development racist.

Like Corbyn, she refuses to condemn violence by any organisation on the Left, and has been overheard many times in private blaming all black London riots on police violence.

