<data key="bio &amp; notes">Founder of Momentum in 2015. Insists all members are also members of the Labour Party. 
See Companies House entry for "MOMENTUM CAMPAIGN (SERVICES) LTD"at   https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/09654873/filing-history

Corbyn’s friend &amp; one of the most important architects of Corbyn’s victory. He was one of only two registered directors of “Jeremy Corbyn Campaign 2015 (Supporters) Ltd.”, the other was Simon Fletcher — who became Corbyn’s chief of staff.

Seen as the man behind Jeremy Corbyn’s rise to prominence, Mr Lansman began life in Southgate, north London, a short drive from the 16th century Highgate School, where he studied between 1970 and 1975.  He went on to study economics at Clare College, Cambridge, where he also ran for president of the students’ union alongside Andrew Marr, the BBC journalist.  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/08/23/labours-public-schoolboys-jeremy-corbyn-accused-hypocrisy-calls/

See also this 2016 article from the Spectator... most interesting. https://life.spectator.co.uk/articles/letting-the-hard-left-off-the-leash/   

When he was 16, Lansman, who was raised in an orthodox Jewish family, left his home in London to work on a kibbutz in Israel.  Lansman would later call his time in Israel a politicising experience, citing the pioneering spirit of the place and the sense of community and radicalism as things that inspired him. He came back to Britain having lost much of his Zionist zeal, but with a newfound excitement about the ways society could be radically transformed. As a young radical, Lansman worked with Corbyn for radical left-wing MP Tony Benn. 

It is not sure Lansman was a member of Militant, but if he wasn't, he certainly sympathised with them. Now he is close to the centre of the LP and stoking for deselection of moderate MPs and seeing a Communist govt in UK.  A protégé of the late Tony Benn and veteran activist in the Campaign for Labour Party Democracy, Lansman’s understanding of the Labour Party’s structures - and their shortcomings, and how they need to be changed to empower the party membership - is second to none. 

There is suggestion Momentum is Militant 2.0... A Middlesex University student Joe Cox tweeted, “I came to a Momentum meeting so I could make up my mind about them for myself. The first speaker is from the SWP…” That’s the Socialist Workers Party, whose Communist Trotskyite members are also banned from Labour. 

Lansman was closely linked to a web of property companies, some of them offshore, used for tax avoidance and community “asset-stripping.”

12 Jan 18, Lansman, Yasmine Dar and Rachel Garnham are all hard left candidates to join the NEC committee which controls the Labour Party. See https://newsocialist.org.uk/labour-nec-elections-support-the-left-slate/  If this happens the hard left will control the LP, begin changes to deselect moderate MPs and continue rapidly down the line to make the LP a communist party. This critical NEC election takes place this Jan weekend, 13-14 Jan 2018. 
Lansman, Yasmine Dar and Rachel Garnham all won places on the NEC:

On 1 March 18 Jon Lansman put his name forward for LP Gen Sec (after the deselection and resignation of Iain McNicol of the GMB Union) and he intends to fight UNITE for the post, which wants Jennie Formby UNITE to take the post. Lansman is acting against the reported wishes of Corbyn. https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/01/momentums-jon-lansman-confirms-run-for-labour-general-secretary
Fascinating insight by Labour Marxists site on this Formby-Lansman contest, suggesting Lansman is moving to the centre! Which he isn't but he is using other unions support because they don't like McCluskey trying to increase UNiTE dominance of the LP http://labourpartymarxists.org.uk/jon-lansman-vs-jennie-formby-whats-going-on/

11 Mar 18, Lansman gave in to pressure from CAC and Len McCluskey and withrdew his candidacy for the post of Gen Sec of the LP. This means Jennie Formby will take the job, for UNITE. Red Len has won, again. 
For the time being. 

Corbyn, Lansman, McDonnell and Shawcroft were greatly influenced by Vladimir Derer who worked tirelessly to replace the influence of the PLP by that of the members themselves, out there, voting for what they want, which is not necessarily at all what the LP MPs want or what Parliament itself wants.  See interesting explan at https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/09/understand-jeremy-corbyn-look-first-vladimir-derer
and on how these people worked on BRIEFING, a radical Left magazine which alongside the CLPD which Derer got established, has been the engine behind Corbynism over the years. 
This originally emerged as a splinter group from the Trotskyist Chartist Tendency. 
Derer and Briefing could be referred to as Neo-Chartists, as they built upon the work of the original radical chartists of the 19th century who sought to bring about transformative change through constitutional reform.  Corbyn, John McDonnell and Christine Shawcroft, who currently sit on the NEC, were all and continue to be leading lights in the magazine.

Lansman wrote a glowing tribute to Derer upon the latter's death. 

See this article about a meeting in 20 March 2017 where Lansman spoke. He emphasised how important the CLPD had been in "democratising" the LP. NB the CLPD was Vladimir Derer's creation. 
"On the role of Momentum, Lansman sees it as giving Corbyn the chance to lead and providing ongoing organisation that will be there for his succession or any attempted challenges. The passing of the McDonnell amendment to make the threshold lower to get MPs on the ballot is now a battleground. It was notable though that listing the CLPs who are currently supporting it, he did not mention what involvement Momentum had." 

Which implies a Brown Shirt type support from Momentum for whoever, Corbyn or his successor, as long as the radical left character is maintained to the satisfaction of Lansman and Momentum. 

This tough support was enunciated by Jon Lansmann 1 Sep 18 when he said: 'As long as there are perhaps between 12 or 25 or 30 people who are very hostile, who are just waiting for Jeremy to go so they can turn the clock back, then...we'll keep having that fight'.
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6121881/Momentum-founder-hints-30-hostile-Labour-MPs-ousted.html

2 Mar 19, there is no love lost between Peter Willsman or Chris Williamson and Jon Lansman. PW and CW make their names for anti-semitism and JL objects, see https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6762703/Jeremy-Corbyns-party-chief-threatens-Momentums-John-Lansman-key-ally.html?ito=amp_twitter_share-related 

