<data key="bio &amp; notes">UNITE union rep on the LP NEC. There are allegations she was Len McCluskey's mistress and the mother of a child by him (see Private Eye Issue No 1465)

Recently appointed as General Secretary of the Labour Party, Ms Formby spent her early years living between Malta, Bath and Salisbury on account of her father’s service in the Royal Navy. Via a grant provided by her father’s employer, she attended Bath High School for GIrls and later St Helen and St Katharine boarding school in Abingdon. Despite receiving a flush of O-levels and A-levels, she opted to go straight into work, stating that she had already grown “fed up with institutions”.  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/08/23/labours-public-schoolboys-jeremy-corbyn-accused-hypocrisy-calls/

After the DSel of Iain McNicol as LP General Secretary and his resignation in Feb 2018, Formby was tipped to take over that role. 

BUT, on 1 March Jon Lansman put his name forward and intends to fight UNITE for the post, against the reported wishes of Corbyn. https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/01/momentums-jon-lansman-confirms-run-for-labour-general-secretary

However, on 11 Mar 18, Lansman gave in to pressure and withdrew, leaving the job almost certain for Formby. Red Len has won this round. 

Private EYE carried a piece on UNITE's manoeuvres in their issue 1465, called Fruit of the Union, quote "Unite is pushing to have Jennie Formby appointed Labour’s next general secretary with a haste that smells of panic. The process took 10 weeks in 2011, but Unite and Corbyn’s office want Formby in by 20 March.

“I have fought for gender equality – often the hard way – throughout my lifetime in the labour movement,” Formby said, posing as the feminist underdog. True feminists may wonder how hard the fight has been when Formby had the good fortune denied to so many women of having been Len McCluskey’s mistress. So torrid was the affair that in 1991 she named the then married Unite boss as the father of her child. Unite later helped her career by giving her the £75,000-a-year post of Unite political director in 2013.

‘Mass walkout’
Nor is Formby always an advertisement for the woozy belief that women in power create kinder workplaces. Gerard Coyne, McCluskey’s defeated rival in last year’s Unite leadership election, can’t bring himself to say her name; and the Politics Home website quoted an unnamed Labour insider saying: “Staff at Labour HQ can’t stand Jennie because she is so divisive and unpleasant.” There would be a “mass walkout” if she won. Meanwhile former Blair-era aide Adrian McMenamin wrote on the right-wing Labour site Progress that Formby’s supporters have made “a mockery of every claim they have ever made about wanting a democratic party”. As a devious Blairite, he said he wanted Formby to win so naïve members would learn how “appalling” their heroes were."

The Formby-McCluskey liaison, which led to a baby between them and her taking a well-paid 75,000 p.a. job in UNITE, was well known and reported upon in 2013...http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2371813/Mother-union-boss-love-child-fixes-MPs-Labour-New-scandal-McCluskey-gives-75-000-year-key-role-ex-mistress.html  

End March 2018, Formby is now the General Secretary of the LP, in the following manner.... 
The previous LP Gen Sec Iain McNicol resigned on 23 Feb 18 after 7 years. http://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/labours-general-secretary-iain-mcnicol-resigns-a8225961.html

He had opposed Corbyn in the 2016 leadership contest arguing MPs should have more say and there are suspicions that his position was made untenable and he was obliged to resign. 
DSel. 

Everyone expected a Corbyn &amp; Co supporter, probably a Momentum person, to take over theis role as the NEC is now controlled by the hard left will decide who to appoint. 

See also http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/02/24/labours-general-secretary-iain-mcnicol-quits-tumultuous-tenure/   

BUT, Lansman put his name forward and in March 2018 a battle developed between Lansman and his supporters and Jennie Formby fronting for UNITE. Allegedly, Lansman even refused to step down when Corbyn phoned him. So the fight developed as a battle between Lansman/Momentum and Formby/UNITE union. See long Marxist analysis in http://labourpartymarxists.org.uk/jon-lansman-vs-jennie-formby-whats-going-on/ 

Jennie Formby won the fight after Lansman steopped down and she is now LP General Secretary. 

Almost the first thing she does is suspend the most senior Jewish member of the LP, Dan Simpson, the secretary of the Parliamentary Labour Party, who had in fact already handed in his resignation because he was disgusted at Formby getting the job, and was working out his notice. http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5584027/Labours-general-secretary-fire-placing-partys-senior-Jewish-official-leave.html

23 Jun 18, Daily Express, There is a claim Formby was once a member of Militant "Mr Crick’s report has been backed up by the Labour Party’s former South-east director Michael Creighton. He confirmed that Ms Formby was a member of Militant in Southampton in the 1980s. “Militant never published a membership list but it was common knowledge at the time among Labour Party members in Southampton that Jennie was a member." See https://www.express.co.uk/comment/expresscomment/978490/Jennie-Formby-Labour-Party-member-Militant

and also fm this DE article, "Militant was a Trotskyist entryist group which attempted to take over the Labour Party. It always denied being an organised body, arguing that it was simply a newspaper. The Liverpool Labour Party – and thus Liverpool council – was controlled by Militant and in 1982 the local Liverpool party agreed to set a deficit council budget, which was illegal.  As a result, a Labour Party inquiry held that Militant was a “separate” and “distinctive” body and membership of Militant became an expellable offence."

10 Jul 19, Jennie Formby, one of Jeremy Corbyn’s closest allies, is at the centre of a fresh row over alleged political interference in the handling of complaints of anti semitism against Labour Party members.  And, Seumas Milne, the Labour leader’s director of communications and strategy, has also been accused of laughing at a former official when they offered advice on how to deal with the party's problems, says Mike Creighton, Labour’s former head of disputes. "Mr Milne “laughed” down his suggestion that Mr Corbyn (should) make a speech on the Middle East which defended Israel’s right to exist.)  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2019/07/10/labours-general-secretary-accused-interference-amid-fresh-anti/

</data>
