<data key="label">Mick Whelan ASLEF</data>
<data key="role">General Secretary ASLEF

his father was a member of the Socialist Workers Party whilst he described his mother's beliefs as "hard Labour".

Total members in 2011 when Whelan was elected were 18,898. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">ASLEF union rep on the LP NEC. Very hard left, strikes, activist, old school techniques.   He is a friend of Gerry Adams. 
https://www.aslef.org.uk/gensec.html

On 6 Jun 2016, Whelan, Cash, Ronnie Draper General Secretary of BFAWU and Doug Nicholls called for British workers to vote to LEAVE the EU
see Mirror article https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/four-union-leaders-argue-brexit-8126878 and INSTANT POLL on Brexit. 

At his election for Gen Sec in Oct 2011, Mick Whelan, 50, regional organiser for Aslef, mainly covering the Midlands, received 3,683 votes, with the union's national organiser Simon Weller getting 3,458. out of a membership electorate of 18,898   So, only 19.45% of the total membership voted for him.  

He is not always the hard working man he likes to portray, see this http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3183327/Dressed-gangster-union-boss-bringing-misery-commuters-120-000-year-chief-claims-represent-ordinary-people-tucked-caviar-party.html  dated 3 Aug 15.

He may say the 2017 deal is good for his members who voted for it with a good turnout, but WSWS does not agree, calling this a "treacherous role of unions".  The left is riven with bitter infighting. https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2017/12/04/asle-d04.html

