<node id="38">
<data key="label">Christine Shawcroft</data>
<data key="role">MP</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">CLP rep on the LP NEC.  CLP MPs (Constituency Labour Party) were perceived as the more left wing faction in the Labour Party.   She is a Director of the MOMENTUM CAMPAIGN (SERVICES) LTD ( https://www.companiesintheuk.co.uk/ltd/momentum-campaign-(services) ) and on the steering committee of eight, an extreme left supporter who was suspended from the LP for supporting the corruption of Lutfur Rahman... See https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/may/11/labour-christine-shawcroft-suspended-lutfur-rahman-tower-hamlets    She is also a supporter of Labour CND, speaking at CND meetings.   16 Jan 18, following Momentum's success putting 3 new members on the NEC committee, Shawcroft is now Chair of Labour's Disciplinary Committee, the NEC Disputes Panel, ousting Ann Black, a more traditional hard left type, 
see http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/christine-shawcroft-replaces-ann-black-as-chair-of-labours-nec-disputes-panel_uk_5a5dfb3be4b04f3c55a5e19c   Late March 2018, a huge anti-semitic fuss burst where Korbyn and teh Labour Party were found guilty of gross anti-semitism. Shawcroft was foolish enough to try and keep on a number of LP people who had all made their anti Jewish views very plain, and she had to resign from Chair of the LP Disciplinary Committee. But she is refusing to quit the NEC.  See  https://uk.news.yahoo.com/labour-discipline-chief-quits-opposing-223625056.html   and  https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/mar/28/christine-shawcroft-labour-disputes-panel-chair-resigns-antisemitism-case    

Corbyn, Lansman, McDonnell and Shawcroft were greatly influenced by Vladimir Derer who worked tirelessly to replace the influence of the PLP by that of the members themselves, out there, voting for what they want, which is not necessarily at all what the LP MPs want or what Parliament itself wants.  See interesting explan at https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2016/09/understand-jeremy-corbyn-look-first-vladimir-derer
and on how these people worked on BRIEFING, a radical Left magazine which alongside the CLPD which Derer got established, has been the engine behind Corbynism over the years. 
This originally emerged as a splinter group from the Trotskyist Chartist Tendency. 
Derer and Briefing could be referred to as Neo-Chartists, as they built upon the work of the original radical chartists of the 19th century who sought to bring about transformative change through constitutional reform.  Corbyn, John McDonnell and Christine Shawcroft, who currently sit on the NEC, were all and continue to be leading lights in the magazine.

</data>
