<data key="role">NEC member</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">CLP rep on the LP NEC. A veteran left winger, old fashioned activist and campaigner.
CLP MPs (Constituency Labour Party) were perceived as the more left wing faction in the Labour Party. 
She is a member of Momentum, elected to the NEC in 2016. 

She was Chair of the NEC Disputes Panel until 16 Jan 18 when Christine Shawcroft, more hard left than Ann Black and now on the steering management committee of Momentum, ousted her with support of the new Momentum presence in the NEC (Lansman, Gar and Garnham). Given Black is a long time campaigner, it will be interesting to see how she continues her support of Momentum after being ousted from this Disputes Committee. </data>
