<node id="40">
<data key="label">Keith Vaz</data>
<data key="role">MP</data>
<data key="follow up">BAME... Black Asian Minority Ethnic</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">A lawyer, barrister, on various committees. Was involved in a sex rent boys scandal, but survived. Is the BAME rep on the LP NEC (BAME = black, Asian, minority ethnic).   Links or support to the IRA? In February 1990, the Provisional IRA bombed a British Army recruiting centre in Leicester and Vaz publicly suggested that the Army had stored explosives on the premises. "Keith Vaz: Minister and networker". BBC News. 26 January 2001. 

12 Jan 18, his position as BAME rep on the LP NEC is at risk. Corbyn has ordered a review of LP "democracy", which is another way of fixing it for Momentum members to consolidate their grip on the LP and the NEC, see https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2018/jan/09/labour-democracy-review-keith-vaz-national-executive-committee-risk   
This review is being led by Katy Clark, Claudia Webbe and Andy Kerr, all Momentum supporters. 

7 Nov 18, Vaz appears again in the news in connection with his alleged enthusiasm for rent boys and because the Commons Speaker used parliamentary privilege to block a freedom of information request from the BBC.. journalists were trying to find out information about Mr Vaz’s behaviour on official trips abroad, during which he was accused of breaking parliamentary rules and bullying staff, see https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6365049/John-Bercow-used-special-powers-cover-claims-bullying-Labour-MP-Keith-Vaz.html

Vaz has doubtful connections with UK passport scandals.  https://order-order.com/?s=keith+vaz+passport+office#gsc.tab=0&amp;gsc.q=keith%20vaz%20passport%20office&amp;gsc.page=1

