<node id="216">
<data key="label">Rosie McCorley</data>
<data key="role">NI AM Sinn Fein/IRA</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">At Aug 2014 pro-FARC activist mtg in Westminster

 Rosaleen "Rosie" McCorley (born 14 January 1957) was born in the Lower Falls but moved “up the road” to Andersonstown at an early age. She is an Irish Sinn Féin politician who was selected by her party as a member (MLA) of the Northern Ireland Assembly to represent the Belfast West constituency in June 2012 and replaced her party colleague Paul Maskey ct.

She was a former prisoner, jailed in 1991 for the attempted murder of an army officer and possession of explosives. She was the first republican woman to be released under the terms of the Good Friday Agreement. 

She was West Belfast’s newest Assembly member. 
see https://www.anphoblacht.com/contents/22294

