<data key="role">TD Sinn Fein/IRA</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">At Aug 2014 pro-FARC activist mtg in Westminster

Emmet was the brother of Frank Stagg, the convicted IRA terrorist, who went on hunger strike until his death in 1976 in Wakefield prison. See https://www.anphoblacht.com/contents/14822

However, Emmet was allegedly anti IRA then. In 1994, Stagg, a senior Labour left-winger, gave a statement in which he admitted he was the politician who had been the subject of recent speculation in Irish newspapers. He accepted his conduct had been 'undoubtedly indiscreet' but not illegal.
Mr Stagg, who is married with two children and has represented Kildare in the Dail since 1987, said he had been sitting in his car alone in Phoenix Park one evening last November when he was approached by a man in his mid- twenties on a bicycle. They had first talked through the window, then the man had got into the car.   https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/irish-minister-set-to-survive-scandal-1427878.html</data>
