<node id="254">
<data key="label">Gerry Adams</data>
<data key="role">Sinn Fein/IRA</data>
<data key="follow up">Explore links of Donaldson's murderers.

What links did he and does he have with John Downey who is finally, as of 5 Feb 2018, facing a civil action for his suspected part in the Hudge Park bombing and death of 4 soldiers in 1982, plus 31 others injured. See the Sun https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/5508386/hyde-park-bomber-john-downey-finally-facing-justice-36-years-after-attack-that-left-four-dead-and-31-injured/ as the Sun has been supporting the families. The Legal Aid dept has refused FIVE times to support the families and the Sun took up their case 9 months ago.  

Explore recent connections between Corbyn's leadership group and Sinn Fein/IRA on the issue of reuniting Ireland, ie handing Northern Ireland over to the South. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">See his Twitter account https://twitter.com/GerryAdamsSF 
See more on Sinn Fein politicians at https://www.britannica.com/topic/Sinn-Fein 
and a timeline history of IRA/Sinn Fein at https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/ira/etc/cron.html 

There are very many of them. This is one political party which unusually, if not uniquely, has seats in two contiguous countries as well as members at the EU Parliament.

Amid all the lies of Adams and Corbyn "working for peace" it is well to remember how Adams continued his walk behind the coffin of the IRA man, Kevin Brady, totaly unperturbed while just close by two British soldiers were dragged from a car and savagely beaten to death, 19 Mar 1988. See the photo of the only Irishman there who cared, Fr Reid.  https://www.irishtimes.com/news/politics/gerry-adams-s-ira-past-crucial-to-peace-1.1608220
 
8 Jan 2018, two murderers of an IRA mole close to Gerry Adams, Denis Donaldson, were reported arrested today. One was a Sinn Fein Councillor.   http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5245779/Two-men-arrested-Denis-Donaldson-killing.html 

26 Feb 18, Adams praises "outstanding" Corbyn and says he should be PM: https://mornbook.com/sinn-feins-adams-backs-outstanding-corbyn-for-pm.html

