<data key="follow up">Who is running the Health and Safety Executive?</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">At Aug 2014 pro-FARC socialist activist mtg in Westminster.

Wrack is very militant and strong supporter of Corbyn but provided good leadership to his members in the dispute with the government over pay, conditions and pensions, and unusually, he got the public on his side. Last year he has led his union back into Labour Party affiliation.

Strike action by firemen in Merseyside in 2006 led to an accusation from the Chief Fire Officers Association (CFOA) that the union was pursuing a political agenda in an attempt to disrupt ‘modernisation’.  http://www.cfoa.org.uk/10346 

See his Bio at https://www.revolvy.com/topic/Matt%20Wrack 

The FBU re-affiliated to Labour after Jeremy Corbyn's election as Labour leader in 2015, over a decade after splitting with the party in protest at the policies of then-leader Tony Blair.

In July 2017 the union said Mr Corbyn was "by far the best candidate for firefighters, for the fire and rescue service and for working people in general"

