<node id="369">
<data key="label">Simon Fletcher</data>
<data key="role">ex-Corbyn's Staff, Union link</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Was Ken Livingstone’s former chief of staff, was formulating strategy and liaising with the unions and activist groups. Fletcher, who served as Ed Miliband’s trade union liaison officer, is widely regarded to have been behind a slew of unions, including Unite, offering Corbyn their endorsement.
See https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/aug/15/jeremy-corbyn-world-supporters-mentors-influences

His job was Director of Campaigns adn Planning. He is very well connected in hard left circles, a friend of Jon Lansman. Fletcher and Lansman set up the company to handle donations to Corbyn in his leadership coup in 2015, “Jeremy Corbyn Campaign 2015 (Supporters) Ltd.” which then changed its name to Momentum Campaign (Services) Ltd. 

Was forced to quit in Feb 2017 by Seamus Milne (and John McDonnell) but remains involved in Momentum.  http://labourpartymarxists.org.uk/jeremy-corbyns-staff-what-was-straight-left/

Bio on him in the Independent.. https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/simon-fletcher-from-communism-to-jeremy-corbyns-consigliere-10508673.html

