<node id="375">
<data key="label">MOMENTUM</data>
<data key="role">Network</data>
<data key="follow up">Alliance for Workers’ Liberty (AWL), a communist Trotskyite group.

Follow up all names at Companies House See Companies House entry for "MOMENTUM CAMPAIGN (SERVICES) LTD"at   https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/09654873/filing-history

Follow up all at http://www.peoplesmomentum.com/ncg 

Check all on steering committee incl Cheesman, Shawcroft etc and what Simon Fletcher does and why he started M with Lansman.

Check out the regional campaign groups at https://unseat.co.uk  and Centre-Left Grassroots Alliance and the LP's National Policy Forum (NPF) How does the NPF relate to the LP NEC?  And "Grassroots Now!"

Check out all regions at http://groups.peoplesmomentum.com  

Check out how Momentum is taking over grassroots classic Labour Party organisations all round the country, at http://www.peoplesmomentum.com/labour_organising   and ID regional groups and people in them. 

Check out Momentum's new "tool" for people to call others to get them to come to meetings, the "Grassroots Now" phone canvassing website. at https://call.peoplesmomentum.com/?_ga=2.238347072.116072873.1518325069-1562421241.1518325069   or, in their words, How to Defeat Tories... WHAT IS THE TORY PARTY DOING ABOUT THIS?

phone-banking. What is this and how does this work?

Study Momentum's aims at http://www.peoplesmomentum.com/about to ID flaws, democratically speaking, eg Momentum is seeking to become an official affiliate of the Labour Party.  

See what happens in investigation by Electoral Commission against Momentum's alleged abuse of the rules. March 2018</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">A Registered Company No 9654873, founded by Jon Lansman &amp; Simon Fletcher in 2015 to support Corbyn's takeover of the LP. 
See Companies House entry for "MOMENTUM CAMPAIGN (SERVICES) LTD"at   https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/09654873/filing-history

In fact, it started as 3 companies, see "Jeremy For Labour Limited", "Momentum Campaign (Services) Limited", and "New Hope For Labour (Data Holdings) Limited" in the very clear and critical Daily Mirror article https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/momentum-killing-labour-party-only-8495661      which compares Momentum's ethics of "participatory democracy", "fair and honest debate", "safety and self expression" with their other side of their members who scream abuse, hurl bricks as well as brickbats, threaten, bully and intimidate.

Transport and Salaried Staff Association, TSSA, has offices near Euston in London which it gave as a telephone / comms center during Corbyn's bid to become leader of the LP and these offices are now the Momentum HQ, at Walkden House, 10 Melton Street, London mw1 2EJ, near Euston Station.   The company is now registered at Kuddus Kamal Solicitors address 3rd Floor, 95-96 Whitechapel High Street London London E1 7RA along with 114 other companies, see https://www.companiesintheuk.co.uk/ltd/momentum-campaign-(services). Kuddus telphone is 020 3540 6332 and fax 020 7247 7785. 

Directors of Momentum are Christine Shawcroft, Samuel Tarry and Professor Cecile Wright. 

See very good &amp; long summary at http://www.businessinsider.fr/uk/momentum-the-inside-story-of-how-jeremy-corbyn-took-control-of-the-labour-party-2016-2/ 

See also http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/labour/12156177/momentum-activists-jeremy-corbyn-labour-purge.html 

The organisation has a eight-member national steering committee. Lansman is one of them, and at least five others hold the kind of extreme left beliefs that represent the worst fears many people have about Momentum. Five of the eight members of Momentum’s new national “steering committee”, have endorsed or taken part in revolutionary or anti-democratic activity, or excused violence (The Sunday Telegraph can reveal)   

They are:

Christine Shawcroft, was suspended from the Labour Party after trying to defend the corrupt, Islamic-extremist-linked mayor of Tower Hamlets Lutfur Rahman.

Marsha-Jane Thompson, who worked with Ben Sellers on Corbyn's leadership social media campaign, was sentenced to 100 hours community service after being charged with electoral fraud.

Michael Chessum was a supporter of the 2010 student riots that led to the Conservative Party's campaign headquarters being smashed up. Also, when he was president of the University of London Union, he banned students and staff from representing the union at Remembrance Day ceremonies, likening remembrance events to "murderers holding special funerals for their victims". He is no longer on the Momentum Steering Committee but heads a list that runs Another Europe.

Cecile Wright, claimed that a rioter who smashed up shops during the 2011 Nottingham riots were targeting the police because of the “neo-liberal economic and social policies applied over the last 30 years”.

Jill Mountford, a member of the Alliance for Workers’ Liberty (AWL) — a communist Trotskyite sect. She was (recently) kicked out of the Labour Party because of this. In 2010 she stood as an AWL parliamentary candidate against Labour's interim leader Harriet Harman. Mountford's campaign attacked Harman for being a "chemically pure Blairite apparatchik, personally responsible for many of the government’s attacks on the working class."

Momentum produced virulent and offensive anti-British Army pamplets / documents at their meeting which paralleled the Labour Party Conference in 2016, called The World Transformed, a "cultural" festival “powered by Momentum” being held as a fringe event at the 2016 Labour Party conference in Liverpool, see http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/momentum-labour_uk_57e80146e4b0e81629aa020c

12 Feb 2018, Momentum BULLY BOYS BROWN SHIRTS. Momentum starting a big drive to recruit more local members to deselect and act as Brown Shirts regionally, locally, http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5379275/Momentum-embarking-massive-recruitment-drive.html  

11 Mar 18, Momentum being investigated  by the elections watchdog over allegations relating to the accuracy of its financial returns in 2017, declared no cash or "in kind" donations worth more than £500, despite organising ACTIVIST TRAINING SESSIONS led BY PROFESSIONAL TRAINERS FROM BERNIE SAUNDERS TEAM IN THE USA. Including... Claire Sandberg, Mr Sanders' director of distributed organising, and Jeremy Parkin, a field organiser for the Bernie 2016 campaign.
see https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2018/03/10/momentums-use-former-bernie-sanders-campaigners-casts-fresh/

The CWU Union, postal workers etc, officially affiliated to Momentum on 23 Aug 17. 

In June 2018, a petition, penned by Tower Hamlets Momentum activist Alena Ivanova, was produced: “We deplore the persistent attacks of the right-wing of the Labour Party and their attempts to weaponise the issue of Brexit against our party leadership.  But we are equally opposed to the Tory Brexit now on offer. "  Her aim is to get Corbyn to back a 2nd Referendum. See https://uk.news.yahoo.com/grassroots-momentum-campaign-stop-brexit-105257526.html

Momentum's grip on the LP is now considerable, its own guide being recommended to new LP members see http://home.freeuk.net/clpd/index.htm#.WzYxnC-Q3rI and http://home.freeuk.com/clpd/170618newmembers.pdf
So, this means the LP is more or less under the control of Momentum?

Which implies a Brown Shirt type support from Momentum for whoever, Corbyn or his successor, as long as the radical left character is maintained to the satisfaction of Lansman and Momentum. 

This tough support was enunciated by Jon Lansmann 1 Sep 18 when he said: 'As long as there are perhaps between 12 or 25 or 30 people who are very hostile, who are just waiting for Jeremy to go so they can turn the clock back, then...we'll keep having that fight'.
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6121881/Momentum-founder-hints-30-hostile-Labour-MPs-ousted.html

Kuddus solicitors only take cash? Sounds a bit fishy, no? https://www.yelp.co.uk/biz/kuddus-solicitors-london

</data>
