<data key="bio &amp; notes">June 2011, Brighton-based Labour party member Alex Craven set up a Facebook page called “Red Labour.”  This social network became crucially effective in the Corbyn takeover of the LP leadership.

https://www.businessinsider.com/momentum-the-inside-story-of-how-jeremy-corbyn-took-control-of-the-labour-party-2016-2?IR=T

Ben Sellers and Max Shanly soon joined him and became key builders of social networking for the hard left. John McDonnell joined forces with them to take advantage of their success. </data>
