<node id="384">
<data key="label">Ben Soffa TSSA</data>
<data key="role">TSSA IT</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Ben Soffa was lent to Corbyn's leadership campaign by TSSA where he was a communications manager. He did two simple things that would channel thousands of newly enthused Corbyn supporters to pay £3.

First he put a button on Corbyn’s campaign website, which allowed people to click straight for the £3 registration. Second, he created an app which meant that even if they were canvassing from home they could input the data of the people they were calling. Most joined Momentum. 

So, he works with/or/to Lansman, McDonnell and others at Momentum. </data>
