<node id="385">
<data key="label">Owen Jones</data>
<data key="role">Journalist</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Jones is arguably the most influential left-wing journalist in the UK and soon became Corbyn’s number one cheerleader in the mainstream press. He is very frequently asked on comment shows, by the BBC, Sky and Channel 4. His connections are far more numerous than shown in this chart. 

He is a ready apologist for Momentum even if he may not be a member, and believes in the re-privatisation of the railways. Close to Mike Whelan, maybe?  

He is also an apologist for Antifa and its violence, having tweeted @owenjones84 "Cheers to the total destruction of fascism. We smashed you in World War II and we will smash you all over again."  Odd phrasing given his dislike of the army which did fight the Nazis in WW2 and his attachment to Sinn Fein/IRA: 

He tours of the country inspiring activists in marginal seats. His prolific writings and tweets make him by far and away the most influential left of centre commentator.

He is a friend of Jayne Fisher, see Guido Fawkes at this site... https://order-order.com/people/jayne-fisher/ and in company of Sinn Fein’s Conor Murphy, who was sentenced to five years in prison for possession of explosives with intent to endanger life in 1982 and Sinn Fein MLA Jennifer McCann (below centre left), who served ten years for shooting an RUC police officer. 

16 Apr 2018, Jones wrote a vitriolic piece about Andrew Neil, saying only the BBC would employ someone so right wing... of course, to attack him BECAUSE he is right wing and make sure everyone took notice of that, especially the BBC, to get the BBC to sack him. See https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2018/apr/11/bbc-andrew-neil-media-politics
It is a measure of how far to the Left Jones is that he calls the BBC a right wing organisation!

Once again, the WSWS did a piece (16 Jul 16) on the hard left supporting Corbyn, whom they really don't like, saying Jones is a fraud. See https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2016/07/16/jone-j16.html    This sees Jones as part of the "professional purveyors of identity politics and postmodernism at the Guardian"

Jones, it is said, is gay. https://www.pinknews.co.uk/2017/05/09/gay-journalist-owen-jones-demolishes-ex-tory-politician-who-wants-to-scrap-equal-marriage/

Anti-semitism... 31 Jul 18, Jones defends, in an oblique way, both the Corbyn position and that of Willsman who has made some rather anti-Semitic remarks. See https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2018/jul/31/council-leaders-float-plans-to-raise-income-tax-or-other-taxes-to-fund-adult-social-care-politics-live  

Jones was a speaker at the Sep 2018  for The World Transformed, the Momentum-backed side meetings at the Labour Party conference. see https://labourlist.org/2018/08/the-world-transformed-reveals-full-line-up-ahead-of-labour-conference/

In March 2019, Jones speaking with Momentum to say that Labour should prepare for a forthcoming GE, in this article https://morningstaronline.co.uk/article/b/momentum-say-prepare-power  

</data>
