but he remains a keen supporter of Momentum, 21 Jun 2018, see https://uk.news.yahoo.com/grassroots-momentum-campaign-stop-brexit-105257526.html

He was a supporter of the 2010 student riots that led to the Conservative Party's campaign headquarters being trashed. Also, when he was president of the University of London Union, he banned students and staff from representing the union at Remembrance Day ceremonies, likening remembrance events to "murderers holding special funerals for their victims"

Also responsible for organising "Another Europe is Possible" through social media and forthcoming demonstrations "Against the Coup" August/Sept 2019. See https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/30/brexit-momentum-protests-led-hard-left-student-union-activist/

