Jill Mountford is a member of the Alliance for Workers’ Liberty (AWL) — a communist Trotskyite sect. 

She was recently kicked out of the Labour Party because of this. In 2010 she stood as an AWL parliamentary candidate against Labour's interim leader Harriet Harman. Mountford's campaign attacked Harman for being a "chemically pure Blairite apparatchik, personally responsible for many of the government’s attacks on the working class."

