<data key="role">LP Deputy Leader</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Not always supporter of Corbyn but follows the trend. Described as having connections throughout the party and as the "ultimate fixer". 

Remarkable how someone as unenthusiastic about supporting Corbyn and who is nor in Momentum has survived, so far anyway (as of 2 Mar 18)

His supporter is Baroness Alicia Kennedy Labour Peer who ran Tom Watson’s deputy leadership campaign. Kennedy is the power behind the throne. A true party insider, she knows "where a lot of bodies are buried". But as Tom Watson’s star wanes, so does Kennedy’s.

Tom Watson is now, Mar 2018, under pressure to hand back some 540,000 pounds donated to him by Max Mosley, an extreme national socialist with a very salacious personal life. Mosley is billed by the media as extreme right wing but in fact is a fascist, a national SOCIALIST... why else would he give so much in donations to Tom Watson in LABOUR? 
