<node id="416">
<data key="label">Guardian</data>
<data key="role">Newspaper</data>
<data key="follow up">Perhaps give all those journalists listed their own node attached to the Guardian node?</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Various writers on The Guardian who support Corbyn's progress...

Katherine Viner is Editor, “You just get the feeling that The Guardian isn’t influencing the debate in the way that it used to.” There’s a distinct lack of innovation in either its print or online offering and we see no reason to change our view this year. It needs to be more than Owen Jones and Polly Toynbee. Is this why she is trending to show more writers from the hard left? She is a very close friend of Seamus Milne.

Anushka Asthan and Heather Stewart, Joint Political Editors. They have confounded those who thought a political editor job-share could never work. They’ve broken big stories and each developed a good media profile.

Polly Toynbee, Columnist. In 2015 she was a surprising Corbyn sympathiser…then she parted company with Corbyn, but now she seems again to be more supportive of the Labour leader. 

Randeep Ramesh Chief Leader Writer, The Guardian A talented writer, Ramesh is seen as one of the most influential voices on The Guardian and is tipped for bigger things.

Aditya Chakrabortty is senior economics commentator for the Guardian. He tweets @chakrabortty. He is hard left and very pro Corbyn. 

Maya Goodfellow, supports CND and is a pacifist.

Steve Richards, left-winger, makes the point that there is no real link between (left wing) protestors and the Marxist Party, attempting to spoil the idea that the current NMLP is driven now by Marxists (7 Feb 18)

Phil McDuff, freelance, but supports hard left positions. 

Maria Margaronis, of Greek descent, born &amp; lived for years in London, writes regularly for the Guardian, radical left, and runs a site called The Nation https://www.thenation.com/subject/politics/   	
She has invoked the extreme disdain of right wing site rightpedia which is toxic about her http://en.rightpedia.info/w/Maria_Margaronis

Hard to know who is right, the World Socialist Web Site, Marxist Leninist, with the Socialist Equality Party, or the neo Marxist postmodernists... see para 13 in this long article https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2016/11/15/reso-n15.html</data>
