<node id="434">
<data key="label">Mike Hedges UNITE</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Hedges, a taxi driver and UNITE union member, ferried Mr Corbyn around in the back of his cab during the 2015 Labour leadership contest.

His partner Jayne Fisher is a former Sinn Fein member of staff who previously worked in Mr Corbyn’s office.

He tried to get selected in Watford but the local people refused to vote for him, so UNITE complained there had been voting irregularities. A revote is expected. http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/12/14/selection-labour-target-seat-centre-unite-union-candidate-row/
Hedges’s candidacy caused controversy earlier this month when Labour’s ruling National Executive Committee imposed him on the final shortlist after Unite complained when he was rejected by the Watford party’s selection panel.

The move led to complaints from local members that the selection was being “rigged” by Unite to ensure Mr Hedges made the shortlist.

In the end, Hedges lost at the final hustings to Chris Ostrowski, who stood in June. 
</data>
