<node id="955">
<data key="label">Laura Murray</data>
<data key="follow up">Check people and links in  Labour Complaints Team </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Laura Murray is a keen supporter of Mr Corbyn, daughter of Andrew Murray and Susan Michie. 

Murray is a Corbyn Adviser who hasmoved to Labour Complaints Team and Is Being Sued By Rachel Riley https://order-order.com/2019/03/04/rachel-riley-suing-labours-new-complaints-adviser/ …

https://twitter.com/GuidoFawkes/status/1102617981316751360

Now, 6 Mar 19, Corbyn has had to back track to say Laura Murray will not be put in charge of complaints. 
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2019/03/06/jeremy-corbyn-backtracks-putting-daughter-adviser-charge-investigating/

10 Mar 19, Laura Murray is back in the news, well, the Sunday Mail, where she is said to be stakeholder manager to the leader of the opposition stands to benefit from the sale of "Le Enfant au Pigeon (Child with a Dove)" by Picasso which was sold for £50million in 2013. Laura 
Murray is being sued by Countdown's Rachel Riley after a Twitter spat. 
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6791735/Family-Corbyn-aide-sued-Countdowns-Rachel-Riley-50m-selling-prized-Picasso.html

10 Mar 19, a Twitter account revealed more on where the Murray's money comes from, confirming the sale of the Picasso... https://twitter.com/Gabriel_Pogrund/status/1104660037702766594
The painting was bequeathed to Murray's maternal great grandmother, Lady Aberconway, in 1947. It was loaned to the public. In 2013, DCMS blocked its sale, deciding it was "probably our most important Picasso".  No buyer could be found, however, and it made its way to Qatar.  

“The government decided the artwork belonged to the many, not the few, and banned its export”

Laura Murray's mother Susan Michie, heiress to more than £50million, started a speech last year with the line: "We the working class..."
</data>
