<node id="862">
<data key="label">Tribune</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Tribune was a democratic socialist fortnightly magazine, founded in 1937 and published in London. It was independent but usually supported the Labour Party from the left. It appeared fortnightly as a magazine, and appears online, under Aneurin Bevan's motto, "This is my truth. Tell me yours". (which in retrospect seems like an early postmodern attitude to objective truth?!) 
Publication of the print version was suspended on 14 January 2018 for "a short break". Publication continued online at www.tribunemagazine.org[1]

https://www.revolvy.com/main/index.php?s=Tribune+(magazine)</data>
