<node id="515">
<data key="label">People's Assembly</data>
<data key="role">Against "Austerity"</data>
<data key="follow up">Follow up all names in the http://www.thepeoplesassembly.org.uk/supporters

Lot of links to communist parties etc 

There is a lot of detail, and it produces data about regions, naming places in the UK where LP activists are on the go. 

list of original supporters https://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/feb/05/people-assembly-against-austerity
</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">The People's Assembly against Austerity. http://www.thepeoplesassembly.org.uk
http://www.thepeoplesassembly.org.uk/supporters

Founded by Tony Benn, Len McCluskey, Corbyn in Feb 2013, it is supported by a large number of hard left activists... s Unite, UNISON, NUT, NUJ, PCS and RMT. It has also received support from numerous campaigning groups, individuals and political parties. 

These include: the Green Party of England and Wales, the Communist Party of Britain, the Coalition of Resistance, Left Unity, Labour MPs and individuals including: Tariq Ali, Imran Khan, Bruce Kent, John Pilger, and Ken Loach.
See open letter in Guardian dated 5 Feb 2013. https://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/feb/05/people-assembly-against-austerity 

A press conference was held on 26 March 2013 in London where speakers included Caroline Lucas MP, journalist Owen Jones,[4][5] comedian Mark Steel, then Labour MP Katy Clark, comedian and disabled activist Francesca Martinez, Steve Turner of Unite and Zita Holbourne representing Black Activists Rising Against the Cuts.

3 Feb 2018, march on Downing St protesting about the NHS, see http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5347705/Ralf-Little-joins-thousands-protest-NHS-crisis.html   All the usual suspects taking part, incl reps from UNITE, GMB, </data>
