It says, "You can’t buy a revolution, but you can help the only daily paper in Britain that’s fighting for one."

Co-operative, reader-owned socialist newspaper. Britain's Road to Socialism, the programme of the Communist Party of Britain, underlies the paper's editorial stance. It was formerly the Daily Worker, before being renamed in 1966.

This paper was, obviously, very supportive of the events around the 200th anniversary of the birth of Karl Marx... and John McDonnell spoke at the Marx 200 events see https://www.morningstaronline.co.uk/article/marxism-a-force-for-change-today-john-mcdonnell-tells-marx-200-conference
