<node id="566">
<data key="label">MOMENTUM KIDS</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">A national initiative set up by Momentum to encourage teachers and carers in early education, those in childcare with caring responsibilities, to be politically active... 

.. and to subvert children at the earliest age. 

See HuffPost on the .. http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/momentum-kids-jeremy-corbyn-labour-party-political-education-creche_uk_57def98be4b05d79137004ab
or this Labour List charming explanation of their aim to politicise your children... on the radical left of course. 
https://labourlist.org/2016/09/momentum-kids-aims-to-make-politics-child-friendly/
and
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/09/19/welcome-to-momentum-kids-where-you-can-live-happily-ever-after-i/

Sasha Josette, one of the founders of Momentum Kids, and Jessie Hoskin, is her co-founder, both from Stroud. Children’s author, Alan Gibbons, was part of the children’s programme at the party conference in 2016.

Another article, in the Guardian, big on irony about this is brainwashing kids https://www.theguardian.com/politics/shortcuts/2016/sep/19/momentum-kids-where-childcare-meets-leftwing-activism  but a further article by Suzanne Moore which totally supports Momentum Kids. 

See the Facebook site... https://www.facebook.com/Momentum-Kids-1729854593932314/   In fact, only 220 people appear to Like this page, but of course there is much made of Corbyn in it and links to the postmodernist neo-Marxist David Harvey.

Check the FB site for updated news on this organisation. 

On 11 June 2019, Corbyn promised, "Austerity is, and always was, a political choice. A whole generation of children are paying the price for Tory cuts.   Labour will deliver 30 hours of free, high-quality and properly funded childcare every week for all two to four year olds."  
ie brain washing in support of radical Labour. 

However, the British public have not so far lunged out to join this plan, as after three years still only 282 people "Like" this page. That would not stop a radical left Labour government from implementing what Corbyn wants to do. 
</data>
