<node id="620">
<data key="label">Trade Union and Socialist Coalition TUSC</data>
<data key="follow up">Check links between TUSC and other CLPs and Momentum</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">TUSC is an extreme hard left group Chaired by Dave Nellist. They are banned, at present anyway, from (maybe only some) CLP meetings. 
http://www.tusc.org.uk

A co-founder, with Nellist, was Bob Crow (now RIP) of the RMT.

Jennifer James lays into Walker for his failure to support a campaign to reinstate three members of the CLP he chairs after they were expelled over allegations that they are members of the Trade Union and Socialist Coalition (TUSC)
https://www.theredroar.com/2018/01/awksbox-ii-skwawkbox-blogger-to-be-deselected-by-local-momentum-members/

Good summary here and check out the references given.  https://www.revolvy.com/topic/Trade%20Unionist%20and%20Socialist%20Coalition&amp;item_type=topic

Prominent trade union support comes from the RMT union. TUSC's co-founder was former RMT general secretary Bob Crow. Leading members of the PCS, NUT, FBU and POA unions are on the steering committee. The most prominent participating groups are the Socialist Party and Solidarity. In the 2015 General Election, TUSC stood 135 parliamentary candidates across England, Wales and Scotland[6] and 619 in the local elections.[7] TUSC did not stand candidates in the 2017 UK General Election as they supported Jeremy Corbyn as leader of the Labour Party</data>
