<data key="bio &amp; notes">Gable and Carpel in Searchlight are alleged to have links to this 62 Group. see http://www.aryanunity.com/bidney.html

This site alleges that Gable was a convicted burglar and that his staff writer Manny Carpel has done time for arson and some form of violence (against what?).

The site also alleges dubious (to put it mildly) links with the 62 Group and the 43 Group, both allegedly quasi criminal gangs... "The 43 Group was politically linked to Herut, and its terrorist arm, the Irgun Zvei Leumi, better known as the Stem Gang. This group murdered and tortured British Servicemen in Palestine in the 1940's. It was founded by one Ze'ev Jabotinsky in 1943 (hence the connection with the '43 Group)."

Another Jewish Marxist in 43 Group was Morris Beckman, see his story at https://poumista.wordpress.com  
Famously, Vidal Sassoon was a member. Sandy Rashtry‘s JC obit explains why it was called the 43 Group:

43 people (38 men and five women) who formed the group at the Maccabi House sports club in Hampstead in 1946. …[By] 1947 [it] had more than 1,000 members in London, Manchester, Birmingham, Leeds and Newcastle….</data>
