<data key="label">Martin Smith</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Controller, writer of Dream Deferred and  political activist.

He has been a left wing activist for decades.  He is a former National Secretary of the Socialist Workers Party (SWP), a position he held from 2004 until January 2011. He left the SWP in 2013.

See also, https://livesrunning.wordpress.com/2013/12/08/martin-smith-a-retrospective-1-loving-music-hating-racism/

Smith joined the SWP in the 1980s and eventually become a member of the Central Committee. He was involved in disrupting talks at Acas in May 2010 between British Airways and the Unite trade union which he defended on Channel 4 News.[3] He has also been involved at a senior level in Unite Against Fascism. 

In September 2010, he was convicted of an assault on a police officer during the protest in October 2009 against British National Party leader Nick Griffin's appearance on Question Time. He was sentenced to a 12-month community order

He is also keen on music, jazz. 

See this film on Youtube about a debate on the differences between the Socialist Party and the Socialist Workers Party https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uAjaEkk3LU8   36 mins of socialist stuff. 

</data>
