<node id="664">
<data key="label">Hunt Saboteurs Association</data>
<data key="follow up">Check links of members with other groups, eg Momentum, SWP etc. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Hunt Saboteurs association is a often very militant, aka violent, group against hunting. 

http://www.huntsabs.org.uk  and they have a Facebook page.

They disrupt hunts, attack riders and then complain shrilly when they are counter attacked. 

Very left wing. 

A web search produces a good deal about this group written up by them or on court cases in which they appear to be the victims, and virtually nothing about why they do what they do and what the effects are on the rural community. 
So, for want of any better site, there is a useful summary at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hunt_Saboteurs_Association   especially note the reference to the offence of "aggravated trespass", refs to notes 9 and 10 in this Wikipedia article.

</data>
