<node id="699">
<data key="label">Brian Cathcart</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Brian Cathcart, a professor of journalism, allegedly received 45,000 pounds from Mosley and other moneys, in his position as Professor of Journalism at Kingston University. 
see http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5479787/Mosley-donations-aid-press-hating-professor-Hacked-Off.html

So Carthcart is being accused of association at the least with the "fascist" Max Mosley, if not actually being a fascist, and therefore of course a racist too.
However, Cathcart is on the Left! He is a regular contributor to the Guardian where his articles are plainly left wing as this page on him in the Guardian shows https://www.theguardian.com/profile/briancathcart 
In fact, like most leftwingers, he supports the Leveson recommendations which are really little more than an attempt to restrict and muzzle the press, stop them publishing material the left find embarrassing. Fortunately, in May 2018, another attempt by Labour to pass Leveson 2 was voted down by Parliament (see also an entry for Tom Watson on this. Ed Miliband also spoke frantically trying to get Leveson 2 accepted)

So, this is another case of the left accusing the left of being fascists! And, of course, they are right!! Fascism is National Socialism.</data>
