<data key="bio &amp; notes">Run by the Communist Party of Great Britain (Provisional Central Committee). 
https://www.weeklyworker.co.uk 

The Weekly Worker is a weekly newspaper published by the Communist Party of Great Britain (Provisional Central Committee). Published since 1993, the paper developed out of The Leninist, a publication inside the old Communist Party of Great Britain which was banned by the leadership.

The paper has a policy of printing critical viewpoints, including those of the party's own membership, and is known for its reporting of (some say gossip about) the actvities of other left-wing groups.</data>
