<data key="follow up">Check background and links on these links and association and particularly the undeniably anti-semitic elements of this. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Corbyn has always been keen on supporting Hezbollah against Israel. 

Some light on the political background of Hezbollah... https://marxistleftreview.org/articles/review-joseph-daher-hezbollah-the-political-economy-of-lebanons-party-of-god/
..."substantial connections between Iranian capital and Lebanese Shi’ites."
1994 essay, "The prophet and the proletariat" by British Marxist Chris Harman, argued that Islamist political organisations attracted support from all classes, but emphasised especially the role of impoverished middle classes.
Hezbollah espouses a brand of Shi’ite Islamism first popularised by Ayatollah Khomeini in the Iranian revolution. It emphasises the need for complete obedience to supreme religious bodies, adherence to strict (Islamic) codes of modesty and propriety, and resistance to the US, Israel and its allies.

Hence, October 23, 1983, Hezbollah used two truck bombs to hit buildings in Beirut, Lebanon, housing American and French service members of the Multinational Force in Lebanon (MNF), a military peace-keeping operation during the Lebanese Civil War. The attack killed 241 U.S. and 58 French military personnel, six civilians, and two attackers.

In Jan 2018, Abbott instructed Labour MPs to vote against a motion to ban Hezbollah from the UK! Her logic is that this motion would have adversely affected peace talks in the Middle East. 
https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/5426591/diane-abbott-orders-labour-mps-oppose-ban-terror-group-hezbollah/

Of course, the real reason is that Hezbollah is a radical left neo Marxist Leninist group so their philosophy is parallel to Abbott's own. 
