<data key="label">Sinn Fein/IRA</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Sinn Féin, (Irish: “We Ourselves” or “Ourselves Alone”) political party that long was widely regarded as the political wing of the Provisional Irish Republican Army (IRA)  See https://www.britannica.com/topic/Sinn-Fein

Corbyn has always been close to Gerry Adams, not "just for a cup of tea" in Westminster as some of his colleagues claim, but because he likes their politics and dislikes British politics. 

Now, should he get into No 10, strong betting he will hand Northern Ireland to Dublin. 

This will suit Sinn Fein IRA and eliminate the DUP from Westminster, reducing Tory support there. 

It will also destroy the UK, as if NI goes to Dublin, the Scots will resume their calls for Independence too, and under an extreme socialist Corbyn government will likely get what they want. 

This node is linked to the April 2014 node because it is extraordinary and inconceivable that so many Sinn Fein/IRA members of the Dublin parliament came over to Westminster just to help the Colombian FARC.  Even just for the all-expenses-paid trip to London would not account for such a turnout. But to see Corbyn and Co and discuss future plans for the British Isles, there is a far more plausible explanation 

</data>
