<node id="731">
<data key="label">SUTR Black Country</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">I don't know who chose the name for this group. See https://www.facebook.com/Black-Country-Stand-Up-To-Racism-1137612022985017/

Where there was a sympathetic article about a Black Panther member who was in prison for 41 years in the US but had his conviction overturned. The Panthers were a particularly nasty and violent group of communists. https://www.britannica.com/topic/Black-Panther-Party

