<node id="780">
<data key="label">Caryl Churchill</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Caryl Churchill is a Patron of Palestine Solidary Campaign.

A major playwright, she has won many awards, including the Obie Sustained Achievement Award in 2001. She worked with the radical theatre companies, Joint Stock and Monstrous Regiment during the 70s and 80s, during which she produced some of her best–known plays (Cloud Nine, Top Girls and Serious Money). In 2001 a performance of her play Far Away supported by the Royal Court raised funds for two Palestinian theatres.</data>
