<node id="811">
<data key="label">David Harvey</data>
<data key="follow up">His connections with other postmodernists and with others in the hard left in the UK.</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Harvey FBA (born 31 October 1935 in Gillingham, Kent) is a British Marxist communist academic. He lives in New York where he is professor of anthropology and geography at the Graduate Center of the City University of New York.  http://davidharvey.org

A long time (neo-)Marxist, he has been applying his communist principles to geography which is his academic subject. He taught at John Hopkins (1969–1987 &amp; 1993 - 2001) where Lyotard was also teaching. Following  Lyotard, Derrida and Foucault he became a Post Modernist and is a post-modernist influence on Corbyn and McDonnell. He was top of the speaker line up at the September 2017 World Transformed public meeting in Brighton. 

He is the author of "The Condition of Postmodernity" (1989: note that 10 yrs before this Jean-François Lyotard wrote his book which was called "The Postmodern Condition: A Report on Knowledge") written while a Professor at Oxford, was a best-seller (the London The Independent named it as one of the fifty most important works of non-fiction to be published since 1945, and it is cited 30,000 times by 2017). It is a materialist critique of postmodern ideas and arguments, suggesting these actually emerge from contradictions within capitalism itself.  (rather than that they emerge from the earlier failures of the classic Marxist workers-bourgeoisie model... remember the Rule of Opposites).

See this review of this book.. http://patrickbrianmooney.nfshost.com/~patrick/presentations/w10/harvey/reading-notes/summary-single.html
 
Highly likely this man's Post Modernist ideas have had considerable influence on Corbyn &amp; Co. He was for example a lead speaker at the World Transformed public meeting in Brighton 23 - 26 Sep 17 with McDonnell, Abbott, Paul Mason and others. 

He is a long time Marxist, see his views on wealth, not that it has upped the standard of living of vast numbers of people but that it has robbed people of their wealth; which by the way they didn't have before capitalism created it. 

See this article about him and on Stanley Fish, another far left postmodernist who is mentioned in Stephen Hicks' book. 

See his interview with Novara https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=utmWYLdZve4  

He was speaker at the Sep 2018  for The World Transformed, the Momentum backed side meetings at the Labour Party conference. see https://labourlist.org/2018/08/the-world-transformed-reveals-full-line-up-ahead-of-labour-conference/  

See Harvey in a Novara video in discussion on Technology and Post Capitalism with  Paul Mason, Aaron Bastani, Alice Bell and James Meadway https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=g18JoOZsoEM</data>
