<node id="814">
<data key="label">John Hopkins, Baltimore</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">PM spread to the US, to John Hopkins University. By Lyotard?, see below. 

David Harvey taught at JH for some time, see https://www.thefamouspeople.com/profiles/david-harvey-7589.php

As did one of the key French postmodern intellectuals Jean-Francois Lyotard. https://www.iep.utm.edu/lyotard/

In fact, Harvey is the author of "The Condition of Postmodernity" 1989 and 10 yrs before this Jean-François Lyotard wrote his book which was called "The Postmodern Condition: A Report on Knowledge"

And Frank Palmeri wrote in 2001. "Other than Postmodern? – Foucault, Pynchon, Hybridity, Ethics" in Postmodern Culture, vol. 12 no. 1, Baltimore: which was published at the Johns Hopkins University Press.</data>
