<node id="816">
<data key="label">Eddie Izzard</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Stood against Lansman, Gar and Garnham to be on the NEC but was beaten by them all, rather inevitably as Momentum control the voting membership. 

So when the anti-semitism row broke and Christine Shawcroft was obliged to stand down on 31 Mar 18 for supporting various people in the LP who were plainly anti-semitic, Monsieur Izzard was put forward to take her place. 

He appears to support Corbyn's platform and quotes, "For the Many, not the Few" but is this for a quiet life or does he genuinely support Corbyn? And does he realise quite how radical Corbyn and Co really are?

