<data key="bio &amp; notes">The Communist Party of Britain is a communist and Marxist–Leninist[13] political party organised in Great Britain and since 2012 has been the sole British representative at the International Meeting of Communist and Workers' Parties.[14] The party emerged from a dispute between Eurocommunists and Marxist-Leninists in the Communist Party of Great Britain in 1988

This party is linked to the Daily Worker, McCluskey's supporting paper, see at https://www.communist-party.org.uk

Notably, the party condemns the air strikes on Syria by US, France and UK, because of course they support all things USSR / Russian. 

The FT was given access to a Communist Party of Britain meeting and spoken to its leader Robert Griffiths, who says there are “no major differences on immediate issues” between his party and Corbyn’s Labour</data>
