<data key="label">The News Line</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">The News Line is a daily newspaper published by a British Trotskyist group, the Workers' Revolutionary Party. It was launched in 1969 as Workers Press[https://www.marxists.org/archive/hallas/works/1985/12/cult.htm] and renamed News Line in 1976.[https://www.worldcat.org/title/news-line/oclc/145398605?referer=di&amp;ht=edition]

For a time during the 1980s, the WRP split into two rival factions, and for a short time there were two versions of The News Line being produced every day, one by each faction. [Newsfeed updated daily online but limited print circulation.]

