<node id="857">
<data key="label">Kate Hudson</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Key speaker in the early meetings of People's Assembly

She is the General Secretary of CND and led a noisy protest at St Paul's Cathedral on Friday 3 May 2019 when Prince William went to a service there to celebrate Britain's nuclear submarines protecting the country for 50 years. 
The protesters, pinned back by a security cordon shouted and chanted. 
CND said it was "horrified" at the service, with general secretary Kate Hudson adding that it was "morally repugnant."
Since April 1969, for 24 hours a day, seven days a week, 365 days a year, at least one UK ballistic missile submarine has been on patrol beneath the waves of the world's oceans as ultimate protection of Britain's people and their security. 
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/05/03/prince-william-booed-heckled-nuclear-deterrent-service/

CND and former member of Communist Party of Britain, and a supporter of Stop the War Coalition. 
