<node id="873">
<data key="label">Die Linke (De)</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">The Left (German: Die Linke), also commonly referred to as the Left Party (German: die Linkspartei, is a democratic socialist political party in Germany. It is considered to be left-wing populist by some researchers. https://en.die-linke.de/welcome/ 

In fact, the party is the most left-wing party of the six represented in the Bundestag, and has been called far-left by news outlets such as the British newspaper The Guardian, but according to the German Federal Office for the Protection of the Constitution (Verfassungschutz), the party is not to be regarded as extremely left or a threat to democracy. However, it does monitor some of its internal factions, such as Socialist Left, as do some states' similar authorities, on account of suspected extremist tendencies.

Corbyn met Katja Kipping the leader of Die Linke on a visit to Germany See more at https://order-order.com/2018/05/10/jezzas-die-linke-stinker/

It is notably a major player in extreme left wing groups which include communists and Marxists, eg Socialist Left and Party of the European Left. 

Check out its links with several far left aka communist and Marxist groups.  It is said Die Linke is directly derived from Erik Honecker's ruling GDR communist party of former East Germany.

Kipping was speaker at the Sep 2018  for The World Transformed, the Momentum backed side meetings at the Labour Party conference. see https://labourlist.org/2018/08/the-world-transformed-reveals-full-line-up-ahead-of-labour-conference/  
</data>
