<data key="bio &amp; notes">Hirsch called for Nelson's Column to be destroyed, because it represented British racism. 
From mixed race parents, she is obsessed with racism and group identity politics. https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-5584069/STEPHEN-GLOVER-Afua-Hirsch-summon-smidgen-gratitude.html  

And tried to have Nelson's column taken down, which did not please some... http://www.freedompost.uk/nelsons-column-stays-rebuttal-to-sjw-fascist-afua-hirsch/


From 2014 to 2017 she was the Social Affairs and Education Editor at Sky News. 

She is making a name for herself by writing material highly critical of British racism, as she sees it, though failing to acknowledge the extraordinary advantages everyone gets and enjoys living in Britain... eg Hirsch, Afua (2018). Brit(ish): On Race, Identity and Belonging. London: Jonathan Cape/Vintage. She was clearly born too late, her message would have been more appropriate decades ago when there really was a problem with racism. 

Somehow presenters feel they have to ask her onto their shows, though she seems to have precious little background to comment on anything much, so Piers Morgan found himself talking to her and asking why she disparages Winston Churchill, as does Lily Allen. see https://www.express.co.uk/celebrity-news/960492/Piers-Morgan-Lily-Allen-twitter-spat-national-heroes-Good-Morning-Britain?utm_source=traffic.outbrain&amp;utm_medium=traffic.outbrain&amp;utm_term=traffic.outbrain&amp;utm_content=traffic.outbrain&amp;utm_campaign=traffic.outbrain

