<data key="label">Prof Greg Claeys</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Claeys wrote a book on Marx and Marxism. Penguin Books, 2018; Nation Books 2018; which, perhaps unsurprisingly, was produced in Greek and Chinese translations. 
In an interview on BBC4 he said, ""No, if we look at his writings... Marx is a pretty traditional democrat all the way through."  What?? Is he seriously inviting us to ignore the hundreds of thousands of Marxists following his ideas who created such catastrophes, death and destruction for so many millions in so many countries? ALL the empirical evidence tells any sensible person Marx had ideas which are a disaster for people. Yet people like Claeys are arrogant enough to suggest that actually he had some jolly nice ideas really, it just needs someone nice to apply what he was really trying to say... 
https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b0b2kpm0

Quite a full description at...
