<data key="label">David Scott</data>
<data key="follow up">Follow up the people he has been writing papers with, at http://open.academia.edu/DScott and see what connections they may have with the radical left in universities. </data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Dr David Scott has worked at the Open University since September 2016 in the Social Policy and Criminology dept at Faculty Member
Liverpool John Moores University. He is a qualified teacher and was awarded an MA (with distinction) in Crime, Deviance and Social Policy from Lancaster University in 1996 and a doctorate under the supervision of Professor Barbara Hudson from the University of Central Lancashire in 2006. 

He is “Against Imprisonment” and argues that prisons are immoral places characterised by institutionally-structured violence and death, reflecting and reproducing social inequalities. Focused on abolitionist action, he calls for peaceful and immanent alternatives grounded in social justice.

His Twitter account https://twitter.com/dgscott2

One tweet was.. Punishment: A failed social experiment -a film which features extensive interviews with world leading Scottish abolitionist thinker Professor Joe Sim and 3 other critical scholar activists on prisons and punishment.  Great resource for students/activists. 

See his entry http://open.academia.edu/DScott</data>
