<data key="label">The World Transformed = Revolution!</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Set up just before the 2017 election, it allowed the Left to spend more than its allowance.

In Sept 2018, Momentum and The World Transformed ran their own sideshow to the main Labour Party Conference, which they described as "The World Transformed - a 4-day politics, arts and music festival running alongside the Labour Party Conference, working to build left power both inside and outside of Parliament. Since 2016 we’ve been mixing big names with the most inspiring grassroots voices and tackling topics that others overlook." See https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/sep/25/people-are-using-the-word-socialism-momentum-activists-hail-a-world-transformed

Sunday Times revelations about this organisation at https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/momentum-sidestepped-rules-to-break-election-spending-limit-kx2dk26f3

The World Transformed runs a festival ambience at its meetings, see https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/momentum-labour-conference-the-world-transformed-jeremy-corbyn-brighton-a7972841.html

NOTA BENE also in the Independent article how McDonnell and Lansman have reduced the threshhold of the number of MPs who need to support a candidate in any leadership contest, from 35 when Corbyn scraped in, to 15 and now to only 10, which critics call the McDonnell amendment. </data>
