<node id="919">
<data key="label">Jean-Luc Melenchon</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">The veteran communist Jean-Luc  Melenchon is leader of La France Insoumise which is the latest version of the French Communist party.  

In the 2017, French presidential election, the party did really quite well, polling 18% of the vote in the first round and reaching fourth place behind the Republicans led by François Fillon which polled 19%. 

Melenchon was a speaker at the Sep 2018  for The World Transformed, the Momentum-backed side meetings at the Labour Party conference. see https://labourlist.org/2018/08/the-world-transformed-reveals-full-line-up-ahead-of-labour-conference/

10 Mar 19, Melanchon writes for the Guardian, https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/mar/10/abandon-foolish-brussels-treaties-emmanuel-macron   He urges all the right things, and advises that, "Europe should no longer have anything to do with the Franco-German alliance controlled by Germany’s Christian Democrats. It humiliates the other 26 EU member states and isolates French people from their natural family in the south." Sure, so how would his version of communism help particularly, given the appalling economic record his ideology has produced so far, over the last hundred years and in countries all over the world where socialism has been an unmitigated disaster. 
Still, in case anyone was in any doubt of his sympathies, he assures us, "We should not fear the Russians, who are our partners." Like Corbyn, McDonnell, Milne and so on then. 

