<node id="923">
<data key="label">Santa Monica</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Some of the Marxist intellectuals who were part of the Frankfurt school came over to Santa Monica in the 1950s so this node is a Grouping. 

see Thomas DiLorenzo talking about about Antonio Gramsci and other Marxists in this... https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1rPNZHfPR88&amp;feature=youtu.be
These intellectuals called their thing the Institute for Marxism, as they reckoned no one in the US would understand what the Frankfurt School meant. 

Thomas James DiLorenzo (born August 8, 1954) is an American economics professor at Loyola University Maryland Sellinger School of Business. In this clip, he explains why Marxists want to destroy western culture. And the reason is, briefly, because western culture has prevented the Marxist revolution taking place, so they are attacking the christian heritage, objective truth and of course capitalism. 

He mentions Herbert Marcusa as one of the leftists at this Institute, who wrote a book called Arrows and Civilisation which became very popular among the radical Left in the 1960s in which he wrote "don't work, have sex", which of course was very well received but he wrote that because he was attacking the very roots of the capitalist (or any other successful) society which depends on people working. </data>
