<node id="929">
<data key="label">Cambridge University</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">CAMBRIDGE University students have turned their back on Remembrance Sunday poppies claiming the flowers which honour the fallen “glorify” war.
https://www.express.co.uk/news/uk/1030033/Cambridge-university-poppy-remembrance-Sunday-student-union

1 May 2019, When Cambridge University announced a new inquiry into its links to the slave trade, many casual onlookers will have assumed “those snowflake students are at it again”.  But Cambridge’s soul-searching over slavery actually had very little to do with its students. The decision came directly from the university’s vice-Chancellor, Professor Stephen Toope. A panel of eight academics will spend two years conducting the inquiry. Their mission is to find links between their 800-year-old university and the slave trade and then, presumably, indulge in some righteous self-flagellation for their predecessors’ sins. The inquiry will probably conclude with a public apology, and some have even suggested that the university will pay reparations.
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/05/01/cambridges-grievance-obsessed-professors-real-campus-snowflakes/  art by George Harrison.
and
Another on the same theme by Dominic Sandbrook... https://www.dailymail.co.uk/debate/article-6978591/DOMINIC-SANDBROOK-course-slavery-abhorrent-Cambridge-dons-guilty-Empire-cowards.html  who writes, "At a time when the headlines are full of the plight of the seas, the menace of discarded plastic and the global emergency of climate change, Cambridge’s vice-chancellor wants to plough precious research money into . . . flagellating his own institution about a trade abolished here in 1807. You’d do well to find a better example of petty parochialism, navel-gazing and sheer irresponsibility.
Yet the most shocking thing is the threat to unmask long-dead scholars who supposedly ‘validated race-based thinking’. Professor Toope plans a historical witch-hunt, in which Victorian dons guilty of offending modern sensibilities will be named and shamed."

These cases, and that of Noah Carl, mentioned again in this article, where Professor Jeff McMahan is trying to gather support to pushback against this prejudice which is stifling free speech in universities. 
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/climate-intimidation-british-universities-afraid-speak-anything/
Noah Carl, a research fellow at St Edmund’s College, Cambridge, was studying the link between genes and intelligence, and was sacked after an investigation into his work triggered by an open letter from fellow academics accused him of “racist pseudoscience”. Carl says he was fired because his research threatened “certain sacred Left-wing values.” Seems pretty clear. 

More nonsense about group identity politics from Cambridge University. Surely they should be able to cope with this intellectually restrictive nonsense better than they are doing? https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/07/01/cambridge-university-accused-racism-allowing-non-black-lecturer/


