<node id="934">
<data key="label">Fiona Onasanya</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Onasanya, 35, is the MP for Peterborough (Dec 2018). She is a fervent supporter of Corbyn and some say she would become Britain's first PM. 
However, she was found guilty of perverting the course of justice. Ironic really, as she was a Labour Whip. 
Plainly, she has a slender grasp of the meaning of objective truth. 
The MP for Peterborough was caught doing 41mph in a 30 zone in July 2017.  She initially told the police Aleks Antipow, a Russian who had previously lived in a house in Cambridge rented by her and her brother, was driving. 
Then she claimed her brother had 'set her up' by providing false information. Clearly no love lost there, then!  Finally a former aide disclosed she visited his house alone, near the scene of the offence, on the night in question.  https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6513885/Bare-faced-deceit-Corbynista-tipped-female-black-PM.html
or
https://news.sky.com/story/labour-mp-fiona-onasanya-found-guilty-for-perverting-the-course-of-justice-11586043
or
This succinct summary in Metro https://metro.co.uk/2018/11/26/labour-mp-faces-retrial-over-speeding-fine-as-jury-fails-to-reach-verdict-8178966/  

29 Jan 19, Onasanya has been sentenced to 3 months in jail, but the judge allowed her the chance of keeping her job as an MP!  https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/01/29/fiona-onasanya-becomes-first-sitting-mp-jailed-almost-30-years/  

31 Jan 19, public uproar that FO refuses to resign her MP seat. So, her sentence which is only 3 months and considered very lenient in all the circumstances, is to be reviewed. MPs must give up their seat if they are jailed for 12 months or more. Plainly, she is taking full advantage: she showed her contempt of the law by lying in the first place, and she is still showing her contempt of the system by refusing to resign as an MP https://www.telegraph.co.uk/politics/2019/01/30/exclusive-fiona-onasanyas-sentence-could-increased-government/

26 Feb 19, then, after only 28 days in jail, she was released, still having refused to resign as a MP. What kind of example does this sorry story set for the general public about their MPs? https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-6744321/Speeding-fine-lie-MP-FREED.html

</data>
