<data key="bio &amp; notes">People who support Venezuela are clearly supporting a Marxist socialist government which has gone horribly wrong. These people blame the USA, of course, but the reality is that the radical socialist aka communist government of Venezuela is to blame for its own corruption and economic ruin. 

This Campaign was started in 2005 in response to an attempted military coup to remove Hugo Chavez. Very many UK trade unions support this as do Labour Party MPs and others on the radical left. 

The sad part is that presumably all these people think the sort of government they support in Venezuela would be a good thing for the UK too? 

On 6th Dec 2013, this Campaign published a letter of support of socialist Venezuela signed by a large number of people one can reasonably assume are all on the left.. "Leading figures from across British society such as Grahame Morris MP (Labour Friends of Venezuela &amp; Venezuela Solidarity Campaign,) filmmaker John Pilger, TUC General Secretary Frances O’Grady, Professor Ernesto Laclau &amp; many others have signed a statement in solidarity with Venezuela"

See https://venezuelanalysis.com/analysis/10219 

Including, Michael Derham, Jayne Fisher, Lindsay German, Bruce Kent, and many others... 

