<data key="label">Prof William Whyte</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">White is a historian, Professor of at St John's College, Oxford, and ordained in the Anglican Church. 

http://www.ox.ac.uk/news-and-events/find-an-expert/professor-william-whyte 

March 2019, he led a project to hire a researcher to look into links St John's College may have had with Britain's colonial past. The college said there were "compelling intellectual and ethical reasons for institutions of higher education to face up to the role they played in the British Empire.”
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/03/21/oxford-college-hires-staff-investigate-colonialism-links-rhodes/   
Whyte, who is leading the project, said colleges needed to be “open” about their colonial links.   “It’s about understanding our history, and making sure we have nothing to hide,” he said.

He is married to Dr Zoe Waxman.</data>
