<node id="973">
<data key="label">Labour Against Private Schools</data>
<data key="bio &amp; notes">Radical Left hatred of individual choice and in particular individuals being able to choose and pay for education has now finally, July 2019, coalesced into a grouping dedicated to doing away with private education and putting all private schools into the State system, whether anyone likes it or not. 
https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2019/jul/09/labour-phase-out-private-schools-britain-inequality-finland    This article was written by Steven Longden who is a Manchester secondary school teacher, a Trafford councillor and executive member of the Socialist Education Association.

17 July 2019, Labour Against Private Schools campaign is using the Twitter handle https://twitter.com/AbolishEton, which pretty much tells you where its bias may be, and is backed by Ed Miliband, the person whose internal Labour rule changes led to Corbyn, McDonnell and the radical left hijacking the Labour Party leadership. 
https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-7256665/Labour-campaign-shut-private-schools-cost-taxpayers-billions.html
and in the Times https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/closing-private-schools-will-cost-millions-labour-is-told-dtnc5766n  

Laura Pidcock, Shadow Minister for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, has also backed the campaign, which has been described as ‘class war’ by the group's coordinator Holly Rigby, who teaches at an inner London state school.

</data>
